        "summary": "Heartbleed (CVE-2014-0160) is a CWE-125 out-of-bounds read in OpenSSL 1.0.1 &lt; 1.0.1g letting any remote unauthenticated attacker read up to 64 KB of server memory per request, potentially leaking private TLS keys, sessions, and plaintext. Every triage signal is maximal: CISA KEV, ~100% EPSS, and 4 public Exploit-DB exploits.",
